data.text:
Yahoo! Answers just sort of snuck up on me. You can tell it is a real Web 2.0 service because it presents itself with three verbs: Ask, answer, discover.

Here is Danny Sullivan on its rise:

In May, Barry Schwartz wrote about Yahoo Answers hitting the 10 million answers posted mark, an impressive accomplishment particularly given the low interest and poor take-up answer search has traditionally had in the U.S. But some new stats add fuel to the idea Yahoo Answers isnâ€™t only bucking the trend but perhaps becoming a social interacting phenomenon like YouTube or MySpace.com. [Look Out Wikipedia, Here Comes Yahoo Answers! Part 1]
